messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path:
- /clients

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- false

Acceptable methods for this endpoint (based on the code, not on framework defaults):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The main Express app mounts the clients router at the prefix app.use('/clients', clientRoutes) (index.js). That makes the full path for router.post('/', createClient) be /clients.
- In routes/clients.js the router registers:
  - router.get('/', getClients)  -> GET /clients
  - router.post('/', createClient) -> POST /clients
  - router.get('/user', getClientsByUser) -> GET /clients/user
  - router.patch('/:id', updateClient) -> PATCH /clients/{id}
  - router.delete('/:id', deleteClient) -> DELETE /clients/{id}
- Only GET and POST are explicitly registered for the path '/clients' in the code, so GET and POST are marked true.
- No explicit HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE or PATCH handlers are registered for '/clients' in the code, so those are false. (Note: do not assume implicit handling by Express or middleware; the determination above is strictly from the explicit route registrations shown.)
